				<div class="postbody">
				The LDS is an interesting institution.  Their big payoff is to become god of your own planet someday...if you're a man.  The best a woman can hope for is to be the "blessed vessel" of her deified husband.
<br />

<br />
Then again, mainstream Christianity can be interpreted to include ascension to godhood or near godhood.  If God is your Father and Christ is your brother...well, you do the math.  Contemporary followers of Christ are supposed to be able to perform miracles, too.
<br />

<br />
So while I agree the LDS seems pretty far out there...Christianity in general can also seem that way.<br />
