				Mormon racism?  Just read the last paragraph in bold if you want to get to the good stuff.
<br />

<br />
This is from page 2 of the same mini-book that arrived on my front door (and the front door of every apartment in my unit).
<br />

<br />
"Eloheim is a polygamist, having many spiritual wives.  the number of wives he has in unknown.  These wives bore to him billions of spiritual babies.  These spiritual children lived with him and his wives in a pre-existent realm.  
<br />

<br />
The pre-existence was a place where every human being born on earth lived as one of these spiritual children.  Eloheim saw that his children needed to advance farther, so he decided it was time for them to take a physical body upon the earth to be tested and tried.  Thus Eloheim called together a council of the gods to decide the destiy of all those who would be sent to earth to learn good from evil.  Two of Eloheims' sons were there: Jehova (the first born and the Mormon Jesus) and Lucifer.  We believed Jesus and Lucifer were brothers, and that they are spiritual brothers to all mankind.
<br />

<br />
Lucifer presented his plan to be a savior of the world.  Getting the glory for himself, he would force all of Eloheim's children to obey and become gods themselves.  Jesus said he would give men their free agancy of choice as on all other planets before.  The council of the gods rejected Lucifers plan and accepted Jesus' plan.  He would become the savior.  Angered, Lucifer led a rebellion in Heaven where he convinced one third of Eloheim's spirit children to rebell with him.  He became Satan and was cast out.  One third of the spirit children who rebelled with him became the demons and were sent to earth where they wree denied physical bodies forever.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mormon doctrine states that during this war in heaven, all of those spirit children of Eloheim who did not for for him came to earth cursed with black skin.  Those who fought less valiantly for god came to earth bleessed with white skin, and those who fought valiantly were born into white, Mormon homes.  Therefore, I felt it was my reward from god to be born in these last days into a white mormon home.</span><br />
